Although there is currently no vaccine to prevent coronavirus disease, there are ways to protect yourself and help spreading the virus to others. READ ALSO: After 14 days in isolation Buhari’s daughter reunites with family DoWash your hands regularly for 20 seconds, with soap and water or alcohol-based hand rub Cover your nose and mouth with a disposable tissue or flexed elbow when you cough or sneezeAvoid close contact (1 meter or 3 feet) with people who are unwellStay home and self-isolate from others in the household if you feel unwell Don’t Touch your eyes, nose, or mouth if your hands are not clean 